paper_abstract: We show that there are graphs with n vertices containing no K-5,K-5 which have about 1/2n(7/4) edges, thus proving that ex(n, K-5,K-5) >= 1/2(1 + o(1))n(7/4). This bound gives an asymptotic improvement to the known lower bounds on ex(n, K-t,K-s) for t = 5 when 5 <= s <= 12, and t = 6 when 6 <= s <= 8.
paper_title: Asymptotic Improvements to the Lower Bound of Certain Bipartite Turan Numbers
